name: Cloud Study Jams 18 - GDG Tipaza
description:
• What we'll do
Join GDG Tipaza This year for Cloud Study Jams !

Study Jams are community-run study groups for students on Google Developers content, on various product topics. it is a great opportunity to bring members of your community together to learn something in person. These trainings will give your community members a specific skill they can use for personal development or career advancement.

We will Learn how to set up development and production environments in the Cloud. Learn how Docker and Kubernetes work, or learn how to process Big Data in the Cloud. Get access to Qwiklabs.com, a Google training tool, free of charge. Get Google-hosted badges for your online profiles, to show potential employers what they know about Cloud computing.

• What to bring

name: GDG Tipaza - Mobile Study Jams 18
description:
• What we'll do
Study Jams are community-organized study groups around Google online developer courses. The goal is to support as many students as possible in completing the course, thereby raising the technical level of the community. The Study Jams for Android for Beginners is best suited for two audiences:
1) those new to programming
2) those with programming experience who have never used Android.

The beginner level of the course allows for a broad appeal. Newbies, students, and experienced programmers new to Android can all benefit from this course.

• What to bring

• Important to know

name: Tensorflow | Machine Learning Study Jams
description:
Bonjour les amis !

Nous sommes très enthousiastes à l'idée de proposer le dernier cours de machine learning de Google, «Machine Learning Crash Course» (MLCC), au GDG Tipaza. Ce cours est destiné à ceux qui souhaitent en apprendre davantage sur ML d'un point de vue pratique et appliqué qui leur permettra d'utiliser l'apprentissage du ML dans leurs projets quotidiens, et qui souhaitent bénéficier de la puissance de TensorFlow enveloppée dans des abstractions pratiques de haut niveau. C'est une excellente opportunité pour les professionnels, les entrepreneurs et les étudiants d'acquérir une expérience pratique dans ML et TensorFlow.

• What to bring
Bien Sure Comme à chaque Study Jams, il faudra ramner vos Laptops

• Important to know
Ce cours vous conviendra, si:
Vous êtes un programmeur. Si vous êtes au moins un peu familier avec Python. Vous n'avez pas besoin d'être un expert.
Idéalement, vous en savez au moins un peu sur l'algèbre linéaire et le calcul.

name: International Women's Day Tipaza 2018
description:
• What we'll do
We are proud to be hosting the 2018 International Women's Day Celebration, a women's tech conference. This event will highlight the stories of our growing female community of designers, developers, and technology entrepreneurs.

Concept : Is marked on from March 8th until end of April every year. In different regions, the focus of celebrations ranges from general respect and appreciation for women to a celebration of women's economic, political, and social achievements. We're proud of the contributions women in technology have made across our industry and across our company. And we're excited by the contributions women continue to make today.

• What to bring
Once accepted bring your invitation

name: Google Cloud Next '18 Extended - GDG Tipaza
description:
What are CloudNext ‘18 Extended events?

Next Extended brings together developer communities around the world to take part in the Next ‘18 experience, either during the conference or even after!
These events run from late July to November 9. Next Extended allows local developers to access exciting Next ‘18 content and engage with the community through local speakers, activities, and hands-on labs.

name: Flutter Study Jams 18 - GDG Tipaza
description:
What?
Flutter Study Jams are Community-run study groups based on the Flutter Udacity Course. Participants learn how to use Flutter to develop high-quality, interactive mobile applications for iOS and Android devices.

Why?
Study Jams are a great opportunity to bring members of your community together to learn Flutter in person and support them to complete the course. Everyone, who completes the course will get a Google-offered Study Jam completion certificate and a profile badge.

name: DevFest'18 - GDG Tipaza
description:
DevFest events cover multiple product areas such as Android, Firebase, Google Cloud Platform, Google Assistant, Flutter, machine learning with TensorFlow, and Mobile Web.

Each DevFest is inspired by and uniquely tailored to the needs of the developer community that hosts it.

While no two events will be exactly alike, each event will, at its core, be powered by a shared belief that when developers come together to exchange ideas, amazing things can happen.

#DevFest18 or #DevFestStories.

name: Material DesignLab - GDG Tipaza
description:
In our designLab We will dive into the design process and learn the visual communication and graphic design principles to apply them in our product customization with the help of the adaptable system of guidelines, components, and tools called Material

Why Material ?
Material supports the best practices of user interface design because it is backed by open-source code, it streamlines collaboration between designers and developers, and helps teams quickly build beautiful products.
